main event: An unidentified flying object was sighted over Yap Island by naval personnel on 6 August 1965.
interesting points: The object was observed approximately 15 degrees above the horizon to the west,The sighting reported a steady, bright light,The object was initially heading approximately 150 degrees true, then stopped and disappeared heading approximately 330 degrees true,The observation was classified as ground-visual,The report concluded with insufficient data for evaluation.
sighted object: one bright light in the sky
